[A good map showing the regions can be found at http://mapsof.net/philippines/philippines-regions-and-provinces. The Zamboagan peninsula is located in the southwestern part of the Philippines on Mindanao, to the west of the Davao region where cVDPV2 has been documented in sewage sampling.

One expects to have AFP (acute flaccid paralysis) cases identified as part of the necessary surveillance activities with the goal of polio eradication. While the 7 cases are still pending laboratory confirmation, it is curious that the official government press release mentions 8 of 15 AFP cases have been ruled out, somewhat suggesting the other 7 are going through secondary testing for confirmation (including genetic testing).

The estimated population of Region 9 in the Philippines was 3 629 783 in 2015, according to the Philippines Statistics Authority (https://psa.gov.ph/content/population-region-ix-zamboanga-peninsula-based-2015-census-population-and-housing).

We await further information as it becomes available.

HealthMap/ProMED map of the Philippines: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6692404,46984. - Mod.MPP]
